  <body>
    <p id="p_fjw_cgk_54b">XML is a storage and interchange format for structured data and is supported by all major
      database systems. <ph keyref="product"/> offers the means for managing the interaction with
      some of the most commonly used databases (both <i>Relational</i> and <i>Native XML</i>
      databases). Through this interaction, <ph keyref="product"/> helps users with browsing,
      content editing, importing from databases, using XQuery with databases, SQL execution, and
      generating XML Schema from a database structure.</p>
    <p id="p_gjw_cgk_54b">The types of connections that are supported in <ph keyref="product"/> include:<ul id="ul_hjw_cgk_54b">
        <li id="li_ijw_cgk_54b" irina="irina"><xref href="ibm-db2-connection.dita#ibm-db2-connection">IBM DB2
            (Deprecated)</xref></li>
        <li id="li_jjw_cgk_54b" irina="irina"><xref href="ms-sql-server-connection.dita#ms-sql-server-connection"
            >Microsoft SQL Server (Deprecated)</xref></li>
        <li id="li_kjw_cgk_54b" irina="irina"><xref href="oracle-xml-db-connection.dita#oracle-xml-db-connection"
            >Oracle Database (Deprecated)</xref></li>
        <li id="li_ljw_cgk_54b" irina="irina"><xref href="postgresql-connection.dita#postgresql-connection"
            >PostgreSQL (Deprecated)</xref></li>
